          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A primary 7Li3+ beam with energies around 25 MeV and",
                "a beam current of 300 nAe hits the primary 9Be",
                "target. The 6He beam is produced by one-proton",
                "removal from 7Li in the 9Be(7Li,6He)10B reaction.",
                "However, the reaction  9Be(7Li,alpha)12B may also",
                "occur in the primary  target, leading to an alpha",
                "contamination of the  secondary beam. The reaction",
                "products are collimated  and enter a solenoid that",
                "focuses the primary 7Li  particles onto a \"lollipop\"",
                "where the 7Li particles  are stopped. Because of the",
                "different magnetic  rigidity, the secondary 6He and",
                "alpha particles do  not hit the lollipop, but reach",
                "the secondary 120Sn  target. Typical beam intensities",
                "are about 10**4 to  10**5 particles per second at the",
                "secondary target  position."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 3.8 mg/cm**2 isotopically enriched (98.29%) 120Sn",
                "target and a  3.0 mg/cm**2 197Au target have been",
                "used as secondary targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "79-AU-197(A,EL)79-AU-197,,DA,,RTH",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "79-AU-197(A,EL)79-AU-197,,DA,,RTH",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "79-AU-197(A,EL)79-AU-197",
                        "target": "79-AU-197",
                        "projectile": "A",
                        "process": "EL",
                        "product": "79-AU-197",
                        "quantity": ",DA,,RTH",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA,,RTH"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Because the",
                "scattering 4He + 197Au  is pure Rutherford at forward",
                "angles in the energies of the present  experiment,",
                "runs with gold targets have been performed just",
                "before and after  every 120Sn run to normalize the",
                "4He + 120Sn cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered particles are",
                "detected and identified in a  system of dE and E",
                "silicon detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 120Sn(alpha,alpha)120Sn elastic scattering cross",
                "section was  measured simultaneously with the",
                "120Sn(6He,6He)120Sn experiment."
              ]
            }
          ],
